text:
108 to 112, 116, 120 West Houston Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Thompson Street, seen from the S.E. corner just after the demolition of the buildings along the south side of Houston Street. At the right the west side of Thompson Street, looking north towards Bleecker Street, may be seen.
December 22, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

94, 96, 100-102, 104, 106 West Houston Street, north side, adjoining and at the N.E. corner of Thompson Street.
February 20, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

Houston Street, west from and including No. 102 West, north side, east of Thompson Street. In the background is seen the western end of this section of West Houston Street, which is the original Houston Street. At its western end Bedford Street begins and runs nearly north, and the second section (originally Hammersley Street) of West Houston Street, which is parallel to King Street, bears off towards the west.
The subway under Houston Street has now been covered over, but is not finished at the time of this picture.
February 20, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
